{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VSEuV5kgmbTVLGXUH2FyTF","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The StatefulSet uses `mongod --config /etc/mongod/mongod.conf`, and the `mongod-config` ConfigMap is mounted at `/etc/mongod`. The config is:\n\nCurrent:\n- verbosity: 2 → need to set 3\n- slowOpThresholdMs: 400 → need to set 800\n- journalCompressor: snappy → need to set zlib\n\nThe approach:\n1. Update the ConfigMap with the new settings\n2. Perform a rolling restart of the StatefulSet (secondaries first, then primary)\n3. For the journal compression change, I need to ensure a clean shutdown since WiredTiger's journal files written with snappy can't be read by a process expecting zlib — a proper restart cycle should handle this.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the actual implementation: the ConfigMap needs updating, but ConfigMap changes don't automatically trigger pod restarts, so I'll need to explicitly restart the StatefulSet. Since it's already configured for rolling updates, I can use `kubectl rollout restart` to cycle through the pods one at a time, restarting secondaries first before stepping down and restarting the primary. For an auth-enabled replica set, I'll need the admin credentials to execute any necessary commands during this process. the rolling restart and then monitor the process to completion.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2052,"cache_read_input_tokens":29675,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2052},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fe31f0ca-40d3-4b8a-9367-82a91ebfee4c","uuid":"e18f49bb-b6b9-4b1b-9e87-6e5c702c7534","request_id":"req_011CcgcgnZh4m1PcocuX98SB"}
